{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "These works primarily treat LLMs as the backbone of sequential recommender systems and fine-tune them within the FedSeqRec framework.",
    "While these approaches use \"efficient finetuning\" methods like LoRA [17], they remain impractical due to several limitations.",
    "First, despite efficient fine-tuning, communication costs are still significantly increased.",
    "Furthermore, the computational resources available to clients (e.g., on-device GPUs and battery power) are insufficient to support LLM training.",
    "Although Zhao et al. [65] address this issue by using split training, the communication overhead becomes much worse since clients must transfer intermediate results for each forward and backward pass."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "While these approaches use \"efficient finetuning\" methods like LoRA [17], they remain impractical due to several limitations.",
    "Although Zhao et al. [65] address this issue by using split training, the communication overhead becomes much worse since clients must transfer intermediate results for each forward and backward pass."
